<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Seller's Guide</title>
	<style>
		body {
			font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
			margin: 20px;
		}
		
		.step {
			margin-bottom: 20px;
			padding: 20px;
			border: 1px solid #ddd;
			border-radius: 10px;
			box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
		}
		
		.step-number {
			font-weight: bold;
			font-size: 18px;
			margin-bottom: 10px;
		}
		
		.step-description {
			font-size: 16px;
			color: #666;
		}
		
		.step-icon {
			font-size: 24px;
			color: #337ab7;
			margin-right: 10px;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>

	<h1>Seller's Guide: 10 Steps to Sell Your Home</h1>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">1. Find a trusted real estate agent</div>
		<div class="step-description">Work with an experienced agent who knows your local market and can guide you through the selling process.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">2. Invest in value-adding improvements</div>
		<div class="step-description">Make strategic upgrades to increase your home's appeal and value, such as new appliances or a fresh coat of paint.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">3. Up your curb appeal</div>
		<div class="step-description">Make a great first impression by tidying up your yard, adding some colorful plants, and giving your front door a fresh coat of paint.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">4. Get a pre-listing inspection</div>
		<div class="step-description">Identify and fix any potential issues before listing your home to avoid last-minute surprises.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">5. Highlight with pro photos</div>
		<div class="step-description">Hire a professional photographer to showcase your home's best features and make it stand out online.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">6. Stage your home</div>
		<div class="step-description">Arrange your furniture and decor to create a welcoming and neutral atmosphere that appeals to potential buyers.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">7. Set the right asking price</div>
		<div class="step-description">Price your home competitively based on its condition, location, and comparable sales in the area.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">8. Remove personal items</div>
		<div class="step-description">Depersonalize your home to make it easier for buyers to imagine themselves living there.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">9. Be ready to move fast</div>
		<div class="step-description">Be prepared to respond quickly to offers and be flexible with negotiations to get the best deal.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">10. Use your head, not your heart</div>
		<div class="step-description">Make rational decisions based on market data and expert advice, rather than emotional attachments to your home.</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>